article.headline: IPFW 80, W. Illinois 71
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- Ben Botts, David Carson and John Peckinpaugh hit consecutive 3-pointers during a 15-2 second-half run that carried IPFW to an 80-71 victory over Western Illinois on Thursday night. Neither team led by more than three points in the first half, and IPFW (8-11, 3-5 Summit) led only 36-35 at the break. The Leathernecks (6-12, 3-5) last led at 48-47 before a 3-pointer by Botts put the Mastodons in front for good. Carson, who led IPFW with 23 points, then hit a 3 and Peckinpaugh added another as the Mastodons continued widening their lead. IPFW went up 62-50 and Western Illinois came no closer than six points the rest of the game. David DuBois led Western with 25 points, while Josh Rivers added 12.
